# Coding standards

## General style

Prefer:
- explicit names
- small modules
- typed interfaces
- predictable control flow
- comments only when useful

Avoid:
- over-abstraction
- deeply nested logic
- magic constants without names
- silent fallbacks

## Naming

Use names aligned with product docs:
- scan
- extraction
- page_type
- confidence
- issue
- recommendation
- limitation
- public_report

## Versioning

Always make versioned constants explicit:
- extraction_version
- scoring_version
- ruleset_version
- prompt_version

## Tests

When implementing core logic, prefer adding tests for:
- extraction normalization
- rules triggering
- score aggregation
- page type detection
- confidence labels

## Refactors

Do not do broad refactors unless asked.
Keep changes scoped to the task.